parameters.description: VPC network domain. All networks inside the VPC will belong to this domain

parameters.description: an optional field, whether to the display the vpc to the end user or not

parameters.description: MTU to be configured on the network VR's public facing interfaces

parameters.description:
IPV4 address to be assigned to the public interface of the network router.This address will be used as source NAT address for the networks in ths VPC.

parameters.description: services supported by the vpc offering

parameters.description: provider to service mapping. If not specified, the provider for the service will be mapped to the default provider on the physical network

parameters.description: desired service capabilities as part of vpc offering

parameters.description: The internet protocol of the offering. Options are ipv4 and dualstack. Default is ipv4. dualstack will create an offering that supports both IPv4 and IPv6

parameters.description: the ID of the service offering for the VPC router appliance

parameters.description: true if network offering is meant to be used for NSX, false otherwise.

parameters.name: nsxsupportlb
parameters.description: true if network offering for NSX VPC offering supports Load balancer service.

parameters.name: enable
parameters.description: set to true if the offering is to be enabled during creation. Default is false

parameters.name: networkmode
parameters.description: Indicates the mode with which the network will operate. Valid option: NATTED or ROUTED

parameters.name: specifyasnumber
parameters.description: true if the VPC offering supports choosing AS number

parameters.name: routingmode
parameters.description: the routing mode for the VPC offering. Supported types are: Static or Dynamic.

parameters.name: physicalnetworkid
parameters.description: the Physical Network ID the network belongs to

parameters.name: vlan
parameters.description: the network implementation uri for the private gateway

parameters.name: bypassvlanoverlapcheck
parameters.description: when true bypasses VLAN id/range overlap check during private gateway creation
